Change to your project directory:
<%= color.bold(`cd ${name}`) %>

To set up your local environment:
* Setup your database with <%= color.bold('yarn db:setup') %>. You will be prompted to create it if necessary.
* Run the app with <%= color.bold('yarn dev') %>. This will start the dev server and watchers for generating types.

<% if (host.name === 'vercel') { -%>
To deploy to Vercel:
* Create a new vercel app by running <%= color.bold('vercel') %>
* Create a staging and production database on Heroku, Digital Ocean, or AWS. Note the URL.
* Visit the settings for the new app in the Vercel dashboard
* Add values for APP_SECRET and DATABASE_URL ENV vars to the preview and production settings
<% } else if (host.name === 'heroku') { -%>
To deploy to Heroku:
<% if (!host.createAppsAndPipelines) { -%>
* Create staging and production apps, databases, and a pipeline to manage them.
<% } -%>
* Enable review apps for your pipeline: <%= color.bold(`heroku pipelines:open ${name}`) %>
* Add a value for APP_SECRET. <%= color.bold('heroku config:add APP_SECRET=mysecret -r staging') %>
* Deploy the app: <%= color.bold('git push staging') %>

<%= color.bold('Repeat with production') %> and you're good to go üëç.
